Got a message midday Friday from my dad's sat phone. Things were bad. No service, no power, water's on the fritz. Trees blocking driveway, truck totaled, house damaged.

I looked at getting a rental to go and help. Every road into Asheville was blocked. Landslides, trees, water.

My brother's house was the same: driveway blocked by multiple trees. One almost took out my niece's bedroom. They fared better than the neighbors though.

They hunkered together, with no info but the scant details we could send his Garmin.

They're safe and well now. But the state of things there hasn't improved much, and it'll take a long time before they do.

The lack of info really got to my family when they were trying to make impossible decisions.

Awful weekend for all of Asheville, western NC, and eastern TN.
